subject: Golf
lead_paragraph: Jeff Maggert and the PGA Tour rookie Brendon de Jonge of Zimbabwe shot rounds of seven-under-par 63 yesterday and share the lead after the first round of the Milwaukee Championship. Maggert eagled the par-5 15th hole and made three birdies on the back nine. De Jonge, who started on the 10th hole, eagled the par-4 second hole and also added three birdies. Garrett Willis was a stroke behind the co-leaders.
